{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04948/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04948"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:49:48"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan, tilt, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["three shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman stumbles giddily up a flight of stairs as a man tries to steady her and an older woman follows behind."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04948","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04948"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/canvas/1/3c349993-d3c7-44b4-b0d4-f3b7c26fc57c","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:38:10.672Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The formal cues quickly signal to us that Barbara Rose is an abject character. Reynolds stands at the top of the stairs and looks down at Barbara Rose, signifying his status and power. Unlike <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW28016955 BCX0\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-00642.html\"><u>Countess Henrietta’s entrance</u></a>, in which the camera moved up the stairs with the client, we are waiting for Barbara with Reynolds, placing her in a diminished position. She comes up to Reynolds; he does not move down for her.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:884.4924759970457,500.08701070901026,489.38123153618915,509.8829855982273"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/canvas/1/ce8f5c92-5345-4084-b27c-87f8d4f76fda","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:38:40.004Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Barbara seems to wobble as she walks up the stairs, requiring her son to steady her when she looks up at Reynolds. This is likely meant to indicate that she is drunk, as her drinking becomes an even more noticeable issue <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW96806712 BCX0\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-05311.html\"><u>later in the film</u></a>, and signifies her general instability.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04948/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:512.6068593057607,391.8639217134416,354.65541912850813,502.66063515509614"}}}]}]}]}